@NODE "ABOUT" "What is Sysop Download ?"
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )·A·b·o·u·t·
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

Sysop DL is a door for all sysops that have lots of users who ask to download
specific files... Imagine how hard it is to pack the files and then upload it to 
your board so that the user can download it..... But now..... The hard work is 
over......  
Just have a look at these great @{"features" LINK "FEATURES"} 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "REQ" "Requirements."                                                        
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )·R·e·q·u·i·r·e·m·e·n·t·s·
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯


A Commodore Amiga computer (Pese suxx :-), /X (I guess any version will do...) 

For this door to work you should also have:
reqtools.library and AEDoor.library in your LIBS:

If U want to use the lha packing feature, U must have lha in your path !
A good place to have it is in C:


If you by any chance should have problems getting this door working, 
then @{"contact me !" LINK "HOWTOCONTACT"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FEATURES" "Features."
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )·F·e·a·t·u·r·e·s·
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

                               

* Fileselector for sysop to choose files from. 

* Online lha crunching (automatic if a directory is selected)  

* Also includes a @{"remote" LINK "DOPUS"} function (With PW protection) for 
cosysops.

* You can now @{"restrict" LINK "RESTRICT"} different files/dirs from being 
downloaded, by putting
  these entries i a file called restrict located in the same dir as this door.  

* This door can now by any time (almost) be exited by pressing Ctrl+c.

* 100% security!

* @{"DOPUS MODE" LINK "DOPUS"} in REMOTE mode!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "INSTA" "Installation."
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )·I·n·s·t·a·l·l·a·t·i·o·n·
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯


                             
Just copy the included files to the correct dirs, that's it.... 
The configuration can be found in the SysDL.info. Here you can choose the temp
dir for lha crunching (The lha file will ofcoz be deleted after the transfer)
The PASSWORD= tooltype contains the password to use if a user is not on the 
remote list.


How to give users axx to remote mode:
USER.X=Username (Where x is a number)
(This is not needed for the sysop who has automaticly access to this...)
For example like this:
USER.1=Preacher
USER.2=UnMad

The username is ofcoz NOT CASE SENSITIVE.

Couldn't be more simple.... (I think)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "USE" "How to operate."
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )·H·o·w· ·t·o· ·o·p·e·r·a·t·e·
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

                              

When you first start the door U will be asked if U want to use the @{"REMOTE" 
LINK "DOPUS"} 
function. This function is included for cosysops etc. ,so if you are local
(In front of your computer :-) U should NOT use this. I'll explain the 
difference between the two modes:

@{i}@{"REMOTE" LINK "DOPUS"}@{ui}
------

@{i}FILESELECTOR@{ui}
------------
If U select Continue from the first prompt, A Nice filerequester will pop up,
and u can select your files or dirs. But before popping up it will check if the 
nodex screen is active, to see if the sysop is around. If not the requester will 
NOT pop up.  
When U are finished, just press OK!, 
and on U go! U are then asked if U would like to Pack the files. If U want that 
then select Pack, else select Continue.... (or Quit)
@ENDNODE

