@NODE "DOPUS" "How to use the REMOTE mode."
                                                               
 _________ 
  _______ )  ·R·e·M·o·T·e ·M·o·D·e··
         )¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
         ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

Users not specified in the sysdl.info will need to enter a password to get axx 
to this feature (sysop&users specified in sysdl.info will automaticly get ax to 
this ofcoz...)

When entering this mode U can select files/dirs by using the cursor keys.
U can select as many items as U like. Pressing any char will make the cursor 
jump
to the first entry starting with that char. (Just as in DOPUS!)

When U are finished, just pressing return, or pressing Ctrl+G will bring up a 
request of what U want to do. 

U can select between: Pack,Continue,Quit...

*Pack will let you LHA pack your files before downloading.
*Continue will download the files without packing.
*Quit will Quit the door (Wow !)

Pressing Ctrl+P from within REMOTE mode, will let you start packing your files
directly.

Have a look at @{"RESTRICTING FILES" LINK "RESTRICT"}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "NEW" "What has changes in v3.3 ?"
